- What is it?

232
00:20:24,595 --> 00:20:27,151
You drove him away?
- He's in the bathroom

233
00:20:27,591 --> 00:20:30,951
You must shoot the guys who
refuse to give a bribe, sir

234
00:20:33,909 --> 00:20:36,751
Mr. Raj Oberoi from Oberoi Towers...?
- What?

235
00:20:37,066 --> 00:20:40,551
Raj Oberoi is the owner of
a chain of 5-star hotels!

236
00:20:40,711 --> 00:20:43,071
How has he got a call from him...?
Give that to me!

237
00:20:46,126 --> 00:20:48,871
Answer my questions
only in yes or no

238
00:20:49,693 --> 00:20:50,731
Yes, okay

239
00:20:50,811 --> 00:20:54,213
Does anyone suspect that you are
Raj Oberoi's nephew?

240
00:20:55,315 --> 00:20:57,351
This chap is Raj Oberoi's nephew!

241
00:20:59,018 --> 00:21:00,159
No, no

242
00:21:00,378 --> 00:21:05,178
You've got to gain an admission here
and serve the whole team for a year

243
00:21:05,618 --> 00:21:09,538
We must send the best of the people
from here for our hotel in London

244
00:21:09,878 --> 00:21:14,138
And keep an eye on Gill, the
manager of the training institute

245
00:21:14,353 --> 00:21:17,283
What for?
- I'm told he's a very capable man

246
00:21:17,483 --> 00:21:21,603
If we could find a man like him,
we can hoist our flag everywhere

247
00:21:22,213 --> 00:21:25,185
Even if we have to pay him 10
times more the salary he's getting

248
00:21:27,034 --> 00:21:31,055
We'll discuss the rest
at dinner tonight, son

249
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:35,253
Was he abusing you?
- He was giving me a job

250
00:21:35,413 --> 00:21:38,053
With ten times more
the salary! In London!

251
00:21:38,622 --> 00:21:41,453
He'll be coming any moment. Go and
arrange for some tea and snacks

252
00:21:41,649 --> 00:21:43,213
Hurry up!
- Remember my promotion, okay?

253
00:21:43,293 --> 00:21:44,493
I take 10 percent

254
00:21:48,053 --> 00:21:50,213
It's okay...

255
00:21:51,087 --> 00:21:56,915
I've seen your certificates, son.
Sit down... please

256
00:21:57,185 --> 00:21:59,196
May I, sir...?
- Please do. Relax

257
00:21:59,276 --> 00:22:02,612
Nothing to worry about.
Things keep falling

258
00:22:02,885 --> 00:22:06,045
When I first came to this institute
for an admission...

259
00:22:06,205 --> 00:22:08,285
I spilt tea on myself!

260
00:22:09,885 --> 00:22:12,845
On a place I couldn't even
apply an ointment!

261
00:22:13,585 --> 00:22:17,125
What would you like to drink...?
- Well...? No, sir, thank you

262
00:22:17,285 --> 00:22:20,861
That's all right. Eat something then.
Our fish-fingers are excellent!

263
00:22:21,034 --> 00:22:24,374
All I want is an admission
and training at yours, sir

264
00:22:24,587 --> 00:22:26,633
But your admission is already done.
- Really sir?!

265
00:22:26,713 --> 00:22:29,547
We need capable boys like you

266
00:22:31,563 --> 00:22:33,547
No, don't cry... don't

267
00:22:36,773 --> 00:22:42,189
Sir, actually I have a friend outside
who's more capable than I am. If he...

268
00:22:42,269 --> 00:22:45,427
So bring him along!
Of course!

269
00:23:03,976 --> 00:23:05,816
Lovely place!

270
00:23:06,736 --> 00:23:10,806
I'll spend every vacation here!
- And I'm thinking of settling here

271
00:23:10,886 --> 00:23:13,315
You must coming visiting me
with your wife and kids sometimes

272
00:23:18,612 --> 00:23:21,228
Something like a girl
is drowning in the sea

273
00:23:21,308 --> 00:23:24,179
Not like a girl...
it's a girl who's drowning

274
00:23:26,655 --> 00:23:29,855
Poor girl... she'll drown
if you don't go to her rescue

275
00:23:30,125 --> 00:23:33,165
Why must I go ? Why not you?
- My mother told me...

276
00:23:33,466 --> 00:23:35,153
never try to save
someone who's drowning

277
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:38,525
You might drown yourself.
- And you're still sending me?

278
00:23:38,725 --> 00:23:40,445
You don't listen to your
mother's advise, do you?

279
00:23:40,623 --> 00:23:44,040
Have you no human feelings...?
If she drowns...

280
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:47,285
I won't be able to face anyone!
- Really?

281
00:23:47,365 --> 00:23:49,045
Oh yes!
- I'll go then

282
00:23:49,125 --> 00:23:50,405
Hurry

283
00:23:52,914 --> 00:23:54,554
What happened?
- My slippers

284
00:23:54,915 --> 00:23:57,714
Oh yes. Or you'll have to pinch
a pair from the temples

285
00:23:58,851 --> 00:24:01,186
What happened now?
- My watch. It'll get ruined

286
00:24:01,266 --> 00:24:03,272
Oh yes, bad times anyway

287
00:24:05,477 --> 00:24:07,477
What now?
- The clothes

288
00:24:07,801 --> 00:24:12,125
Take them off. Strip.
And hurry up. She'll drown

289
00:24:14,331 --> 00:24:15,682
Listen, Chantu...
- What?

290
00:24:15,855 --> 00:24:17,757
Your undies will get wet.

291
00:24:17,837 --> 00:24:19,037
A girl's dying...

292
00:24:19,117 --> 00:24:20,384
and you're worried
about my undies!

293
00:24:21,984 --> 00:24:26,957
Coming... don't worry!

294
00:24:29,689 --> 00:24:30,849
Not very close

295
00:24:33,347 --> 00:24:34,609
Get her hair

296
00:24:35,725 --> 00:24:37,569
Pull!

297
00:24:45,737 --> 00:24:47,489
So simple

298
00:24:48,450 --> 00:24:49,682
Come.

299
00:24:54,126 --> 00:24:55,736
Is she okay?
- Yes.

300
00:24:55,816 --> 00:24:57,315
Check her.

301
00:25:04,709 --> 00:25:06,472
Okay...?
- Are you okay?

302
00:25:11,361 --> 00:25:13,041
If it wasn't for you, I'd have...

303
00:25:14,266 --> 00:25:15,521
I'd have died

304
00:25:16,331 --> 00:25:19,521
Are you staying in this hotel?
- Yes

305
00:25:20,450 --> 00:25:22,947
Your stay and food is
all for free from today

306
00:25:23,131 --> 00:25:26,061
How come?
- I'm the owner's daughter

307
00:25:27,585 --> 00:25:29,865
That's a huge loss!
- Hang on... let me see

308
00:25:30,395 --> 00:25:33,861
If we could have a wad instead...?

309
00:25:33,941 --> 00:25:35,825
Wad...? I don't understand

310
00:25:36,053 --> 00:25:38,265
Actually, we're here for
the management training

311
00:25:38,475 --> 00:25:40,065
So our food and stay is anyway...

312
00:25:41,221 --> 00:25:44,825
I'm here for the training too! We'll
keep seeing each other for a year!

313
00:26:13,367 --> 00:26:17,727
She had you drenched and
left us high and dry, Chantu

314
00:26:17,946 --> 00:26:20,007
Oh yes, this was terrible

315
00:26:21,103 --> 00:26:24,174
I will teach you everything
that is necessary...

316
00:26:24,254 --> 00:26:27,763
for the success of any
5-star hotel

317
00:26:28,178 --> 00:26:31,538
Once you have done this course, you
can go to any hotel in the world...

318
00:26:31,658 --> 00:26:34,618
use my name and land
the manager's job

319
00:26:34,898 --> 00:26:37,898
Bantu, my son... you're listening?
- Yes, sir

320
00:26:40,357 --> 00:26:44,978
This course is part of the
hospitality industry

321
00:26:45,304 --> 00:26:48,224
How does a hospital figure
in the hotel trade?

322
00:26:48,464 --> 00:26:51,144
Hospitality means to
tend to the guests

323
00:26:51,504 --> 00:26:52,784
Taking care of the guests

324
00:26:53,914 --> 00:26:56,904
The five-star hotels are visited
by top bureaucrats...

325
00:26:57,071 --> 00:27:02,304
millionaires... how to treat them
is an art in itself

326
00:27:02,487 --> 00:27:05,224
Something I will teach you today

327
00:27:07,178 --> 00:27:11,913
Chantu, stand up.
Suppose I'm a rich customer...

328
00:27:11,993 --> 00:27:15,254
and you're the waiter.
I visit your hotel...

329
00:27:15,334 --> 00:27:18,224
show me how you're
going to behave with me

330
00:27:24,911 --> 00:27:27,311
Bhola, water to table number 9.
Clean the mess at number 4

331
00:27:27,514 --> 00:27:29,049
Collect 12.50 from the guy
in the glasses

332
00:27:29,129 --> 00:27:32,351
What do I bring for you, sir?
Roast mutton, lentil-curry...

333
00:27:32,530 --> 00:27:34,671
chicken biryani...
what will you have?

334
00:27:35,579 --> 00:27:38,311
This is a 5-star hotel,
not a roadside eatery!

335
00:27:38,551 --> 00:27:40,111
The customer will run away
at this rate!

336
00:27:41,125 --> 00:27:43,951
You sit here.
In the customer's place

337
00:27:45,946 --> 00:27:49,351
Sundri... you show him, dear

338
00:27:58,613 --> 00:28:02,173
What will you have?
- How corny could it get!

339
00:28:02,412 --> 00:28:04,973
That's good, dear.
Go back and sit down

340
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:10,100
May I come over, sir...?
- No, son...

341
00:28:10,180 --> 00:28:13,380
you're going to become
a manager straightaway

342
00:28:13,460 --> 00:28:14,660
No, you relax

343
00:28:14,887 --> 00:28:18,460
Why don't you show us how one
is supposed to behave, sir?

344
00:28:18,725 --> 00:28:20,606
Of course, I'll show you

345
00:28:20,686 --> 00:28:24,380
Know what? You sit here...
and I'll give you a performance

346
00:28:26,974 --> 00:28:28,700
Pay attention, everybody

347
00:28:43,592 --> 00:28:48,032
Damn you, baldie!
I don't know any English!

348
00:28:48,192 --> 00:28:50,712
Forget everything else.
Do you have jhunka-bhakar...

349
00:28:50,792 --> 00:28:55,712
Kolhapuri ratla and vada pav?
Bloody big mouth!

350
00:28:57,752 --> 00:29:00,314
Forget everything, brother

351
00:29:00,498 --> 00:29:03,432
You got makki-di-roti
and sarson da saag...?

352
00:29:03,817 --> 00:29:05,255
No, we got pasta

353
00:29:05,428 --> 00:29:10,801
To hell with the pasta!
We got money. Here you are

354
00:29:11,547 --> 00:29:13,341
Here you are

355
00:29:15,054 --> 00:29:18,254
Actually, you can also have
customers like him at times

356
00:29:18,334 --> 00:29:22,614
That is when you must attend to
them with a smile like mine

357
00:29:22,774 --> 00:29:24,195
Class is dismissed

358
00:29:29,989 --> 00:29:32,894
He called me a waiter
in an Irani eatery...

359
00:29:32,974 --> 00:29:35,534
and we made him an attendant
at a Chinese eatery

360
00:29:35,614 --> 00:29:38,494
And he told me, "You'll become
the manager straightaway!"

361
00:29:38,702 --> 00:29:43,654
Wasn't it fun, manager...?
It's gonna be a riot!

362
00:29:44,627 --> 00:29:47,179
When he gets to know that
forget about a 5-star hotel...

363
00:29:47,259 --> 00:29:50,894
your father can't even start a
tea-stall, what will he go through?

364
00:29:54,379 --> 00:29:57,534
Small-fry... eh?
Now see...

365
00:29:57,614 --> 00:30:00,734
how this small-fry makes you
dance to his tunes!

366
00:30:04,896 --> 00:30:08,536
So he got into my office and
made a proper fool out of me?

367
00:30:08,696 --> 00:30:12,416
A sucker is okay, sir.
He made a fool out of you!

368
00:30:12,496 --> 00:30:14,065
They made you cut
a sorry picture!

369
00:30:14,271 --> 00:30:18,055
You think you're very smart...
but he rubbed your nose in cowdung!

370
00:30:18,228 --> 00:30:19,965
Really? You seem
to be loving it?

371
00:30:20,304 --> 00:30:23,125
They still don't know
what stuff I'm made of

372
00:30:23,645 --> 00:30:26,205
You're a real scoundrel, sir.
They don't know

373
00:30:29,085 --> 00:30:30,765
You got it right, son

374
00:30:31,245 --> 00:30:33,285
They've taken only
an admission

375
00:30:33,732 --> 00:30:36,285
But I'm the one who will give
them marks during the test

376
00:30:36,685 --> 00:30:40,365
The tests I put them to...
they'll go for a toss!

377
00:30:40,845 --> 00:30:42,125
Get to work

378
00:30:42,791 --> 00:30:44,685
Now they get to face
the music!

379
00:30:50,056 --> 00:30:55,365
That you and your team have
found the time...

380
00:30:55,525 --> 00:30:58,294
to visit our institute from London,
we are indeed very grateful

381
00:31:00,164 --> 00:31:01,724
You have seen the institute

382
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:06,444
Our students will now
present to you various...

383
00:31:06,684 --> 00:31:07,564
Dishes

384
00:31:07,970 --> 00:31:12,564
Yes, they will present dishes,
you must taste and give them marks

385
00:31:13,181 --> 00:31:14,364
Bring the dishes

386
00:31:32,641 --> 00:31:35,601
What are you making...?
- An Indian burger

387
00:31:36,281 --> 00:31:37,921
Indian burger...? How?
- Simple

388
00:31:38,081 --> 00:31:40,161
Buy a few vada-pavs
from the roadside...

389
00:31:40,281 --> 00:31:42,441
make a nice design
on the bun...

390
00:31:42,681 --> 00:31:46,041
decorate it with a few
onions and tomatoes...

391
00:31:46,554 --> 00:31:47,841
The Indian burger is ready!

392
00:31:51,018 --> 00:31:52,601
What happened?

393
00:31:52,823 --> 00:31:55,081
What happened to her?

394
00:31:56,218 --> 00:31:59,721
My lentil-curry is burnt!

395
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:04,361
There's going to be
a scandal today!

396
00:32:05,635 --> 00:32:10,392
I'll fail... what am I to do?
- Stop crying first, please

397
00:32:11,516 --> 00:32:13,268
I feel like crying more!

398
00:32:19,228 --> 00:32:21,068
I had worked so hard!

399
00:32:21,981 --> 00:32:23,188
Scandal!

400
00:32:24,628 --> 00:32:27,988
It's time for the presentation!
God! What am I going to do?

401
00:32:28,068 --> 00:32:30,148
Hang on... I have an idea

402
00:32:30,228 --> 00:32:33,722
You present his porridge and
he'll present your lentil-curry

403
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:37,468
Why're you messing it up for me?
- You once saved her from drowning

404
00:32:37,628 --> 00:32:39,988
You must save her again...
say yes!

405
00:32:40,148 --> 00:32:42,388
He has said yes!

406
00:32:42,468 --> 00:32:45,028
It's okay... get going!

407
00:32:48,588 --> 00:32:50,228
Come, I'll give you the porridge

408
00:32:50,308 --> 00:32:53,808
Looks like his goose
is getting cooked!

409
00:32:55,506 --> 00:32:59,463
For Sundari this Kheer.
And for Chantu this Daal.

410
00:33:04,137 --> 00:33:08,297
Khurana, till today, we were too
scared to taste a student's dish

411
00:33:09,225 --> 00:33:12,377
And they're having a go at it.
- They're lapping it all up

412
00:33:12,497 --> 00:33:13,697
Eat it up

413
00:33:14,272 --> 00:33:18,237
Try the porridge our
students have made

414
00:33:18,317 --> 00:33:20,117
You'll be left licking your fingers

415
00:33:21,128 --> 00:33:22,877
You laced it, haven't you?
- Oh yes, sir

416
00:33:23,085 --> 00:33:26,437
Half a kilo of salt and
a kilo of laxative

417
00:33:28,357 --> 00:33:32,157
Once they've eaten the porridge,
give away their rooms to others

418
00:33:32,448 --> 00:33:35,324
Why?
- They're going to remain in the loo

419
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:39,237
The boys will now land
a big egg!

420
00:33:39,713 --> 00:33:42,197
Sir, the porridge has arrived!
- Really?

421
00:33:49,874 --> 00:33:51,972
How did the name of Mr. Khurana's
daughter land on the porridge?

422
00:33:52,052 --> 00:33:56,068
Yet another ruse they've used.
- And it'll do us in!

423
00:33:58,868 --> 00:34:01,597
Excellent porridge!

424
00:34:09,154 --> 00:34:11,314
Porridge... this is the
one I spoke about

425
00:34:11,571 --> 00:34:14,954
Are you going to do that
to the whole of it...?

426
00:34:15,236 --> 00:34:17,434
Are you going to polish off
all the porridge!

427
00:34:17,830 --> 00:34:20,314
No, sir... Only I am
eating this

428
00:34:21,344 --> 00:34:23,614
May I give your room away, sir?
- Why?

429
00:34:23,694 --> 00:34:25,474
You're going to remain in the loo!

430
00:34:34,588 --> 00:34:36,194
Give them the bowl!

431
00:34:44,704 --> 00:34:49,106
Why's he acting like a glutton?
- So he's not exposed

432
00:34:49,463 --> 00:34:52,864
His sidekick had laced your
porridge with salt and laxatives

433
00:34:53,193 --> 00:34:56,987
I saw him doing that and decided
to give your dish to Saundarya

434
00:34:57,766 --> 00:35:00,966
But why would he do that?
- We'll get to know tonight

435
00:35:20,350 --> 00:35:22,123
How many times...?
- 21

436
00:35:22,203 --> 00:35:23,420
What are you saying?

437
00:35:23,733 --> 00:35:25,221
You've been to the loo
21 times already

438
00:35:25,301 --> 00:35:27,236
Looks like silver jubilee
is coming up

439
00:35:27,409 --> 00:35:31,334
At this rate, the golden jubilee
is not very far either

440
00:35:32,426 --> 00:35:35,189
You asked me to ruin
their porridge...

441
00:35:35,431 --> 00:35:37,269
and look at what
they've done to you

442
00:35:37,349 --> 00:35:40,269
You're right.
This is a huge betrayal

443
00:35:40,815 --> 00:35:42,955
They first fooled me
and took an admission...

444
00:35:43,035 --> 00:35:46,629
they now force the porridge on me
and make a beggar out of me!

445
00:35:47,885 --> 00:35:51,831
Pade, do something... please!
- Want me to get red undies?

446
00:35:51,911 --> 00:35:57,109
Red undies...? What for?
- Red stops the biggest of trains...

447
00:35:57,189 --> 00:36:00,199
what's this?
- This train's brakes have failed

448
00:36:00,372 --> 00:36:03,269
No train is stopping now!

449
00:36:04,426 --> 00:36:05,749
22 !

450
00:36:06,372 --> 00:36:08,989
At least shut the
door properly, sir

451
00:36:09,183 --> 00:36:12,349
Bantu, we've been exposed!

452
00:36:12,970 --> 00:36:16,130
We've escaped this time.
But he won't spare us next time

453
00:36:16,490 --> 00:36:21,730
Before that time arrives,
let's shut him up permanently

454
00:36:22,112 --> 00:36:25,250
How?
- Just wait and watch

455
00:36:37,834 --> 00:36:40,634
Mr. Gill ! Save me!
- From whom?

456
00:36:40,754 --> 00:36:41,832
From ruin!

457
00:36:45,034 --> 00:36:47,754
I had run away from home
with my boyfriend

458
00:36:47,972 --> 00:36:50,514
He promised me the moon...

459
00:36:50,837 --> 00:36:54,354
but once he had his fun,
he ran away from here

460
00:36:54,714 --> 00:36:58,434
He didn't even settle the hotel bills!
I somehow managed to get out of there

461
00:36:58,772 --> 00:37:02,741
But I don't have money to return
home nor any shelter for the night

462
00:37:05,034 --> 00:37:07,914
Mr. Gill, I've come to you
with great hopes

463
00:37:08,234 --> 00:37:11,034
I'm told you have a heart
as vast as the oceans...

464
00:37:11,314 --> 00:37:16,297
And?
- And you let the rivers flow unto you

465
00:37:16,554 --> 00:37:18,514
It's only a matter of
a single night

466
00:37:18,714 --> 00:37:20,474
I will make some arrangement
for myself tomorrow

467
00:37:20,554 --> 00:37:25,194
No, you needn't worry at all. I'm the
one who'll have to do something now

468
00:37:25,454 --> 00:37:28,634
You can spend as many nights
in my room as you wish to

469
00:37:29,281 --> 00:37:33,274
Say that again, Mr. Gill!
I can't believe my ears!

470
00:37:34,546 --> 00:37:36,234
It's okay, it's okay...

471
00:37:36,567 --> 00:37:39,114
no girl is shelterless
when she's with me

472
00:37:39,486 --> 00:37:41,714
Let me show you... my room

473
00:37:43,994 --> 00:37:45,794
Shall we?
- Oh yes

474
00:37:46,634 --> 00:37:48,354
Come... come on in

475
00:37:48,914 --> 00:37:52,874
I didn't ask you your name.
- Nada Dhill

476
00:37:53,034 --> 00:37:55,754
Nada Dhill...?
- Nadia Dagar Singh Dhill

477
00:37:57,118 --> 00:37:59,114
Your parents knew even when
you were a child...?

478
00:37:59,474 --> 00:38:01,794
Lovely name... Nada Dhill.
My name's Gill

479
00:38:02,512 --> 00:38:08,274
I know you're a decent man.
But your wife's not around, is she?

480
00:38:08,434 --> 00:38:11,354
Where will my wife come from?
I'm not married yet

481
00:38:11,474 --> 00:38:13,554
Really? And how about the servants?

482
00:38:13,756 --> 00:38:16,154
The servants won't come here
until I ask them to

483
00:38:16,405 --> 00:38:20,951
God, I'm scared! You won't try to
rape me because I'm alone, will you?

484
00:38:21,031 --> 00:38:24,954
Not at all! How can I even
touch you unless you consent?

485
00:38:25,034 --> 00:38:30,994
Why not...? If you say it's
very hot and latch the door...

486
00:38:31,074 --> 00:38:31,914
One minute!

487
00:38:33,354 --> 00:38:36,314
Switch on the a/c...
it's switched on anyway

488
00:38:38,474 --> 00:38:41,914
Set your bag on the chair
and make me sit on the bed

489
00:38:41,994 --> 00:38:42,934
Come on!

490
00:38:43,139 --> 00:38:45,554
Looks like the left side
is your favourite!

491
00:38:45,714 --> 00:38:47,314
Sit down.
- One minute

492
00:38:48,631 --> 00:38:53,994
The telephone here...
move it away quietly

493
00:38:54,194 --> 00:38:58,594
take off your coat,
loosen your tie...

494
00:38:58,674 --> 00:39:00,634
may I do it for you...?
- Go ahead

495
00:39:02,729 --> 00:39:06,914
Now look in my eyes say,
"Will you cooperate with me?"

496
00:39:07,453 --> 00:39:09,594
I'd be so scared,
how will I say no?

497
00:39:10,177 --> 00:39:12,634
Listen, will you
cooperate with me?

498
00:39:12,714 --> 00:39:16,394
There you are! I knew it!
All men are alike!

499
00:39:16,775 --> 00:39:20,575
"He makes life miserable...
the wretched Gill"

500
00:39:20,775 --> 00:39:25,695
The wretched Gill...
- You sing so well. Come here!

501
00:39:25,775 --> 00:39:26,945
Come to me!

502
00:39:27,194 --> 00:39:29,375
Sing for me just once!

503
00:39:30,913 --> 00:39:32,307
Come...

504
00:39:33,724 --> 00:39:35,064
Look, don't climb over me!

505
00:39:35,897 --> 00:39:38,135
Help! Is someone there?

506
00:39:38,215 --> 00:39:40,535
I've fallen!
- Fallen...?

507
00:39:41,129 --> 00:39:43,375
Don't sleep on me, okay?
- No!

508
00:39:47,172 --> 00:39:48,935
Sir... what are you doing?

509
00:39:50,123 --> 00:39:51,691
Save me.

510
00:39:51,864 --> 00:39:55,815
I'm so happy you're here!
This old fossil was raping me!

511
00:39:55,895 --> 00:39:59,118
Gill, this boy will
beat you to pulp!

512
00:39:59,420 --> 00:40:02,575
Chantu... you?
Hello

513
00:40:02,797 --> 00:40:06,717
Where did I see you earlier, sir?
And do you stand now?

514
00:40:06,944 --> 00:40:10,037
She's lying!
I've only given her shelter!

515
00:40:10,117 --> 00:40:12,637
Who's going to believe you
once she starts screaming, sir?

516
00:40:14,966 --> 00:40:16,237
She'll yell!

517
00:40:17,669 --> 00:40:19,557
Help!

518
00:40:20,523 --> 00:40:23,680
Help!
- Shut up! Shut up!

519
00:40:25,468 --> 00:40:29,853
Why must I shut up just like that?
- Oh, I see!

520
00:40:31,777 --> 00:40:32,468
Help!

521
00:40:32,548 --> 00:40:34,296
She's a bitch, sir.
You got some money?

522
00:40:34,376 --> 00:40:38,388
Give it to me...
this is no time to count

523
00:40:38,751 --> 00:40:40,348
All of it...?

524
00:40:40,621 --> 00:40:43,265
Here you are. You'll keep your
mouth shut now, won't you?

525
00:40:43,345 --> 00:40:47,108
This will only control my tongue.
But my mouth will remain open

526
00:40:47,453 --> 00:40:48,708
Big mouth!

527
00:40:48,978 --> 00:40:51,108
Give that gold chain!
- Why?

528
00:40:51,188 --> 00:40:53,168
She'll create a scene!
- Help!

529
00:40:53,248 --> 00:40:55,767
Take it away!
- The watch...

530
00:40:55,847 --> 00:40:56,476
Help me.

531
00:40:56,556 --> 00:40:58,698
I'll save your honour!

532
00:41:00,816 --> 00:41:03,428
Here you are. Another sound
from you and I'll strangle you!

533
00:41:04,385 --> 00:41:06,428
Gill, go to hell!

534
00:41:14,068 --> 00:41:16,908
What have you done, Chantu?
You gave her all my belongings?

535
00:41:17,188 --> 00:41:20,508
How can you say such a thing, sir?
If news of this had leaked...

536
00:41:20,708 --> 00:41:23,588
the students would have treated you
like a pariah and spat at you!

537
00:41:24,385 --> 00:41:26,028
No!

538
00:41:26,108 --> 00:41:28,748
The management would have
kicked you out, I say!

539
00:41:30,450 --> 00:41:32,461
Really?
- Oh yes, sir! Yes!

540
00:41:32,647 --> 00:41:35,727
Thanks, Chantu. You've saved me
from a grave predicament

541
00:41:36,007 --> 00:41:39,007
You have no idea how much
I hate blackmailers, sir

542
00:41:39,207 --> 00:41:41,772
Now go and take a cold
shower, sir. Please

543
00:41:42,483 --> 00:41:44,425
Yes, I'll take a shower

544
00:41:52,928 --> 00:41:58,226
There are robberies everyday!
Watches and purses...

545
00:41:58,306 --> 00:42:02,861
mobiles and chains!
And you're doing nothing!

546
00:42:02,941 --> 00:42:07,036
I'm doing my best, sir.
- My foot!

547
00:42:07,509 --> 00:42:12,685
At this rate,
we'll go to the dogs!

548
00:42:38,551 --> 00:42:41,085
Working nights really
is exhausting, isn't it?

549
00:42:41,165 --> 00:42:44,551
We get no sleep and
there's no time to take a bath

550
00:42:44,751 --> 00:42:48,151
Gill's class will begin and he'll
get an excuse to yell if we're late

551
00:42:48,353 --> 00:42:48,991
Yes.

552
00:42:49,251 --> 00:42:50,751
So what are we doing to do?

553
00:42:54,018 --> 00:42:58,591
I think this room is vacant.
I'll go and take a bath...

554
00:42:58,671 --> 00:43:01,951
you stand here. Afterwards, you
take a bath and I'll stand guard

555
00:43:39,585 --> 00:43:40,883
I'm coming!

556
00:43:45,197 --> 00:43:47,517
What happened...?
Where's the injury?

557
00:43:48,237 --> 00:43:50,237
Here... ? Here...?

558
00:43:51,037 --> 00:43:52,757
Maybe on the knee?

559
00:43:53,499 --> 00:43:54,837
Where is it then?

560
00:43:56,576 --> 00:43:58,477
Here.
- Wow!

561
00:43:59,447 --> 00:44:04,127
Clean up this room. I'll check 354,
there's a problem with the tap

562
00:44:28,060 --> 00:44:32,500
Take a hot bath!

563
00:44:33,047 --> 00:44:37,216
Take a hot bath!

564
00:44:41,999 --> 00:44:46,556
A jacuzzi is so much more fun!

565
00:44:51,940 --> 00:44:53,740
Where is it...?

566
00:45:18,753 --> 00:45:20,553
Khanna...
- Yes, Khurana...?

567
00:45:21,753 --> 00:45:24,793
As I was saying...
- How'd I know what you were saying?

568
00:45:25,233 --> 00:45:27,593
That...
- What?

569
00:45:29,233 --> 00:45:34,193
That thing... which is broken...
let's do it to that

570
00:45:35,111 --> 00:45:37,473
Aren't you ashamed to talk
like that about your wife?

571
00:45:37,633 --> 00:45:40,474
Because she has grown old,
you want her to die?

572
00:45:40,647 --> 00:45:43,795
Khanna, what are you talking about?
It's that thing...

573
00:45:43,950 --> 00:45:45,753
in which that thing
came the other day

574
00:45:46,751 --> 00:45:49,953
That thing which, even before
it started, faced that

575
00:45:51,075 --> 00:45:52,713
Are you talking about
the health resort?

576
00:45:54,729 --> 00:45:56,073
Don't even talk about
the health resort

577
00:45:57,140 --> 00:45:59,433
Whenever we talk about it,
my health starts worsening

578
00:45:59,723 --> 00:46:02,713
But we have so much of that
stuck in it

579
00:46:04,469 --> 00:46:07,033
Why don't we do that to it?

580
00:46:07,692 --> 00:46:11,273
Yes, I understand. We have a lot
of money blocked in it

581
00:46:12,059 --> 00:46:14,993
Why don't we sell it?
Of course...

582
00:46:15,346 --> 00:46:19,039
but who would want to buy it?
- Look, and you find Him...

583
00:46:19,119 --> 00:46:20,233
can't you find him then?

584
00:46:20,686 --> 00:46:22,993
Why don't we give a that
and see?

585
00:46:25,756 --> 00:46:29,433
You mean we can even find God.
So why won't we find a sucker?

586
00:46:30,038 --> 00:46:31,919
You mean, we must issue an
advertisement and see?

587
00:46:33,227 --> 00:46:36,193
Go ahead and give it.
Have posters pasted everywhere!

588
00:46:48,137 --> 00:46:51,097
In this hotel, you're...?
- A housekeeping manager

589
00:46:51,817 --> 00:46:53,537
I look after the upkeep
of the rooms

590
00:47:45,302 --> 00:47:46,471
Who went into the room?
- I, sir

591
00:47:46,551 --> 00:47:50,665
Out with the watch. Go on!
- I didn't take it, sir. I swear

592
00:47:54,892 --> 00:47:56,462
I'll check

593
00:48:09,129 --> 00:48:10,569
I apologise on his behalf

594
00:48:12,340 --> 00:48:13,409
I swear, sir...

595
00:48:13,994 --> 00:48:15,108
Get out!

596
00:48:16,481 --> 00:48:19,249
One moment!

597
00:48:20,009 --> 00:48:21,969
Without an investigation,
you cannot fire him

598
00:48:22,049 --> 00:48:24,609
I'm not a cop to
investigate thieves

599
00:48:24,689 --> 00:48:27,489
You aren't a judge either to
go around punishing people

600
00:48:27,811 --> 00:48:29,289
Great dialogue, Chantu!

601
00:48:29,930 --> 00:48:32,809
I'm very sure! He's the one
who committed the theft!

602
00:48:32,979 --> 00:48:36,136
That's a wrong allegation, sir.
Nikhil is being framed

603
00:48:36,355 --> 00:48:40,155
How can you be so that
to say he's not that?

604
00:48:41,867 --> 00:48:44,907
You guys are speaking as if
you know who the real thief is!

605
00:48:44,987 --> 00:48:47,267
Yes, we know him, sir.
- What?

606
00:48:47,984 --> 00:48:49,187
Sit down

607
00:48:49,882 --> 00:48:52,762
Who is it?
- There are just two people...

608
00:48:52,882 --> 00:48:55,922
in this resort who go
tip-toeing around...

609
00:48:56,082 --> 00:48:59,002
like he or he does.
- What do you mean?

610
00:48:59,172 --> 00:49:02,082
Either the owner
or the thief!

611
00:49:04,682 --> 00:49:05,602
Who is it?

612
00:49:12,048 --> 00:49:14,442
Listen... send Monica in here

613
00:49:16,058 --> 00:49:21,345
Have you any personal experience
of Monica spying around...?

614
00:49:26,869 --> 00:49:29,031
A very bad experience, sir.
A terrible one

615
00:49:29,246 --> 00:49:30,246
Really?

616
00:49:32,717 --> 00:49:35,486
They say that you are either
a thief or the boss

617
00:49:35,566 --> 00:49:37,846
Now tell us the truth. Who are you?
- What...?

618
00:49:43,820 --> 00:49:49,269
How did you guys get to know
that I'm his daughter?

619
00:49:49,442 --> 00:49:50,406
What?

620
00:49:52,047 --> 00:49:55,006
You mean, she's...?

621
00:49:55,485 --> 00:49:57,326
your daughter?
- Trapped!

622
00:49:57,604 --> 00:50:00,447
They're going to kick us
out of the institute!

623
00:50:00,620 --> 00:50:02,296
What...?
- Nothing, sir

624
00:50:02,457 --> 00:50:06,617
Actually, we had to do that
during the security training

625
00:50:07,137 --> 00:50:10,937
I'm glad you have
an eye on me

626
00:50:12,545 --> 00:50:15,017
Your daughter

627
00:50:15,247 --> 00:50:17,475
Indeed. Mr. Khurana's only child

628
00:50:17,704 --> 00:50:21,664
Actually, there have been
complaints of theft at the resort

629
00:50:22,459 --> 00:50:26,104
And Monica had returned from Europe
after four years of training

630
00:50:26,459 --> 00:50:28,464
And we knew that no one
recognises her here

631
00:50:28,984 --> 00:50:32,584
We took advantage of that and
made her part of the staff

632
00:50:33,224 --> 00:50:37,384
So that we'd nab the thief and
she'd gain some experience too

633
00:50:37,744 --> 00:50:38,504
Right?

634
00:50:39,529 --> 00:50:43,904
I am suspicious about Mr. Gomes too.
But accusing him without evidence...

635
00:50:43,984 --> 00:50:46,464
will make the staff panic.
- In that case...

636
00:50:46,696 --> 00:50:48,870
if Mr. Gomes is indeed a thief...

637
00:50:49,217 --> 00:50:51,937
he'll be presented to you with
all the stuff he has stolen, sir

638
00:50:52,113 --> 00:50:52,937
What?

639
00:50:55,237 --> 00:50:58,457
Sir, at least try us out

640
00:51:02,502 --> 00:51:04,497
Who's disturbing me...?

641
00:51:07,271 --> 00:51:09,991
Who's this?
- A well-wisher

642
00:51:10,168 --> 00:51:11,791
Why've you called
so late in the night?

643
00:51:12,589 --> 00:51:15,606
Bad news. You can't wait
for happy times

644
00:51:15,686 --> 00:51:19,130
Your bad times have begun.
- What do you mean?

645
00:51:19,210 --> 00:51:24,431
Bantu and Chantu have got to know
that you are the real thief

646
00:51:24,591 --> 00:51:26,791
What...?
- That's not all

647
00:51:26,911 --> 00:51:30,431
They're going to raid your place
with the help of the police tomorrow

648
00:51:31,454 --> 00:51:33,911
You have time till tomorrow morning

649
00:51:34,914 --> 00:51:38,151
Stash away the booty.
Or you'll get exposed!

650
00:51:38,979 --> 00:51:40,911
I'll hang up now

651
00:51:42,989 --> 00:51:44,471
Disconnected!

652
00:51:46,240 --> 00:51:50,760
I must fix the stolen stuff!
The stolen stuff...

653
00:51:50,935 --> 00:51:53,840
all the stuff!
- I don't understand.

654
00:51:55,939 --> 00:51:57,040
Stolen stuff!

655
00:51:58,708 --> 00:52:01,680
What are you doing?
- Put in all the jewellery

656
00:52:03,760 --> 00:52:07,320
I'm a Madrasi from room number 306.

657
00:52:07,400 --> 00:52:12,080
Yes? Go ahead.
- I want 10 plates of idlis

658
00:52:13,919 --> 00:52:18,880
Swami, it's 1:30 in the morning.
Is this any time for a snack?

659
00:52:19,259 --> 00:52:22,640
I've just arrived in a train
from Madras. I'm hungry

660
00:52:23,160 --> 00:52:26,697
Hungry, all right.
I'll send it to you

661
00:52:27,022 --> 00:52:28,960
Keep waiting.
And don't call again

662
00:52:30,276 --> 00:52:32,240
Who was it...?
- A wrong number! Let's go!

663
00:52:34,005 --> 00:52:35,151
What to do now.

664
00:52:39,076 --> 00:52:40,266
Hurry up!

665
00:52:40,346 --> 00:52:42,060
What are you saying?
- Go there.

666
00:52:45,480 --> 00:52:50,520
I forgot to order chutney...
how much will the bill be?

667
00:52:50,640 --> 00:52:53,440
My friend, don't worry
about the bill

668
00:52:53,715 --> 00:52:56,960
After midnight, we serve idli
and sambar without any cost

669
00:52:57,304 --> 00:53:01,725
But you must wait for an hour.
Okay? Please don't call again

670
00:53:02,406 --> 00:53:05,120
The knife!
- Give it to me!

671
00:53:10,936 --> 00:53:14,612
Why're you tearing the mattress?
- Shut up! You don't know

672
00:53:15,649 --> 00:53:18,120
Where is it...?
Here

673
00:53:18,990 --> 00:53:22,341
Take that. This one too

674
00:53:25,487 --> 00:53:27,141
The flour...
- Want some bread?

675
00:53:27,221 --> 00:53:31,780
Shut up! The flour container!
- In the flour? What?

676
00:53:31,860 --> 00:53:36,514
The watches!
Go and get them!

677
00:53:38,222 --> 00:53:41,920
Since the idli-sambar
is on the house...

678
00:53:42,440 --> 00:53:44,840
make it 20 plates instead of 10

679
00:53:45,379 --> 00:53:51,160
My friend, I'll bring 22 plates
of idlis to you tomorrow

680
00:53:51,240 --> 00:53:54,352
The two of us will have
breakfast together

681
00:53:54,432 --> 00:53:59,595
We'll eat and play...
but don't call up again!

682
00:54:00,903 --> 00:54:04,520
The things he has stuffed everywhere!
I can't figure out anything

683
00:54:04,709 --> 00:54:07,000
I'm going to go mad with this man!

684
00:54:17,044 --> 00:54:19,800
Hurry up and lock it

685
00:54:23,228 --> 00:54:25,995
Where are you going with a bag
early in the morning, Mr. Gomes?

686
00:54:26,434 --> 00:54:30,954
Nowhere really. My mother-in-law
isn't keeping well...

687
00:54:31,270 --> 00:54:34,206
so I'm going to look her up
at my in-laws' place

688
00:54:34,286 --> 00:54:37,119
The police are here to take you
to your in-laws

689
00:54:45,086 --> 00:54:46,697
You're trying to
fool us, Mr. Gomes?

690
00:54:46,777 --> 00:54:49,234
You're going to stash
away the stolen stuff?

691
00:54:49,443 --> 00:54:50,834
Go ahead

692
00:55:19,238 --> 00:55:21,558
They're the ones
responsible for this

693
00:55:22,038 --> 00:55:27,260
I will surely return to
settle scores with you!

694
00:55:27,340 --> 00:55:29,420
We'll wait for you, Mr. Gomes

695
00:55:29,620 --> 00:55:30,580
Move it

696
00:55:33,163 --> 00:55:36,940
Gomes looked like a rat
looking into a cat's face

697
00:55:37,020 --> 00:55:41,140
No, he looked like a goat
looking into a tiger's face

698
00:55:41,336 --> 00:55:44,260
That's a nice one, I say.
Here they come...

699
00:55:45,995 --> 00:55:50,914
You've caught the thief, no doubt.
But we've lost something too

700
00:55:50,994 --> 00:55:52,979
What?
- Our hearts

701
00:55:53,059 --> 00:55:57,282
We don't catch petty thieves.
- We even know the thieves' names

702
00:55:57,362 --> 00:55:59,100
So go and catch them

703
00:55:59,180 --> 00:56:00,900
Gotcha!

704
00:56:01,368 --> 00:56:03,100
Gotcha!

705
00:56:51,713 --> 00:56:52,713
"Love..."

706
00:56:53,889 --> 00:56:54,981
"love..."

707
00:56:55,856 --> 00:56:57,510
"love..."

708
00:56:58,094 --> 00:57:00,602
"we've fallen in love"

709
00:57:00,872 --> 00:57:03,833
"Love..."

710
00:57:05,045 --> 00:57:06,713
"love..."

711
00:57:07,073 --> 00:57:09,073
"we've fallen in love"

712
00:57:09,433 --> 00:57:11,513
"Love is catastrophe,
love is intoxication..."

713
00:57:11,673 --> 00:57:13,753
"love is trust,
love is faithfulness"

714
00:57:13,833 --> 00:57:16,033
"Love is life,
love is every happy happiness..."

715
00:57:16,113 --> 00:57:18,365
"love is worship,
