01:51:21,595 --> 01:51:24,715
"That's because my figure..."

1421
01:51:25,296 --> 01:51:28,500
"is 54, 48, 56"

1422
01:51:37,881 --> 01:51:40,413
Who are you?
Let me go!

1423
01:51:48,031 --> 01:51:49,075
Nice arrangement.

1424
01:51:56,922 --> 01:52:00,278
Why have you guys stopped?
Keep playing the band

1425
01:52:00,769 --> 01:52:01,835
I'll play with them

1426
01:52:17,015 --> 01:52:18,177
Boss, you?
- What is this?

1427
01:52:18,454 --> 01:52:20,035
You want to kill him...?
Go ahead

1428
01:52:28,279 --> 01:52:29,875
What are you waiting for...?
Thrash him!

1429
01:52:38,422 --> 01:52:41,930
Baldie, you're hanging
on to a girl...? Go there!

1430
01:52:43,327 --> 01:52:45,161
Why're you shaking?
You got an itch...?

1431
01:52:45,776 --> 01:52:49,235
Look at your size and hers...
go and get him!

1432
01:52:58,438 --> 01:53:02,340
Smartass! As if I get my hands
on you every day!

1433
01:53:02,624 --> 01:53:04,499
Show the temper there!

1434
01:53:09,535 --> 01:53:10,515
You're on their side!
- Oh yes

1435
01:53:38,932 --> 01:53:41,665
Don't you touch them!

1436
01:53:42,246 --> 01:53:44,467
Want me to leave fingerprints?
- Damn you!

1437
01:53:58,880 --> 01:54:00,515
Take them to the hospital!

1438
01:54:03,474 --> 01:54:07,062
You bloody manager! I sent you
to wreck the hotel!

1439
01:54:07,142 --> 01:54:09,345
And you wrecked our own guys?
You want me to break you now?

1440
01:54:09,425 --> 01:54:11,047
Who told you?
- Who told me?

1441
01:54:11,127 --> 01:54:14,875
You hit Kallu so hard, he went
through the glass door!

1442
01:54:15,237 --> 01:54:17,973
You hit Sukhdev so hard,
he fell in the bar counter...

1443
01:54:18,053 --> 01:54:20,075
and everything fell on him!
- And?

1444
01:54:20,155 --> 01:54:23,867
You kicked Raju so hard,
he rammed into the cupboard...

1445
01:54:23,947 --> 01:54:26,515
and everything fell on him!
- So what do you gather?

1446
01:54:26,764 --> 01:54:30,696
What have I to gather?
- Your guys live off you

1447
01:54:30,776 --> 01:54:32,635
They'll recover in a couple of days

1448
01:54:32,859 --> 01:54:35,355
But think of the losses caused
to him in the arson and breakage

1449
01:54:35,502 --> 01:54:37,841
I've dealt him a blow of
at least a million and a half!

1450
01:54:38,034 --> 01:54:39,826
How can you say such things!

1451
01:54:40,110 --> 01:54:45,435
Amazing guy! You make me profit
even in his losses! - Then.

1452
01:54:50,235 --> 01:54:54,675
Look at that! The place was
swarming with beautiful girls...

1453
01:54:54,881 --> 01:54:56,995
and it's as deserted as
a bald man's head today

1454
01:55:00,222 --> 01:55:03,795
"Goa's best hotel"
- Goa's biggest ruins!

1455
01:55:11,439 --> 01:55:14,155
Why's he laughing?

1456
01:55:14,316 --> 01:55:16,274
His ruin has driven him mad

1457
01:55:18,875 --> 01:55:22,155
Who're they...?
- Looks like the insurance guys

1458
01:55:22,792 --> 01:55:26,535
What happened?
- We have inspected the losses

1459
01:55:26,840 --> 01:55:30,520
We'll have to pay at least
5 million as insurance cover

1460
01:55:30,707 --> 01:55:34,554
5 million! But he bought
the policy only a few days ago!

1461
01:55:35,502 --> 01:55:37,446
He had the place insured already

1462
01:55:37,859 --> 01:55:41,419
Can't help it, sir. I'll have to
put together a new disco altogether

1463
01:55:41,659 --> 01:55:44,641
I'll have to get the glass
from Belgium...

1464
01:55:44,807 --> 01:55:47,409
disco lights from America...

1465
01:55:47,548 --> 01:55:49,588
a quality sound system
from London...

1466
01:55:51,159 --> 01:55:53,459
See? He wants us to listen!

1467
01:55:53,927 --> 01:55:56,307
He wants us to be jealous, Sayba

1468
01:55:56,391 --> 01:55:58,991
All this will cost money.
Isn't it, sir?

1469
01:55:59,185 --> 01:56:02,951
But it will surely be
the number one disco! What say?

1470
01:56:03,412 --> 01:56:04,951
Let's go in, Sayba

1471
01:56:09,591 --> 01:56:13,517
Chantu, what will your
mummy and I do in Goa...

1472
01:56:13,597 --> 01:56:16,991
at this age, leaving behind this
house and everything here?

1473
01:56:17,154 --> 01:56:18,953
You've grown old, not me!

1474
01:56:19,343 --> 01:56:24,263
Piping hot tea every morning, dad!
Followed by a continental breakfast

1475
01:56:24,343 --> 01:56:26,184
And relaxation in a
luxurious room after that

1476
01:56:26,264 --> 01:56:30,004
After that, a small dip
in the swimming pool...

1477
01:56:30,142 --> 01:56:34,782
How will your mother get into the
swimming pool at her age, my son?

1478
01:56:34,862 --> 01:56:37,511
As if your mother will!
Give me the phone!

1479
01:56:37,591 --> 01:56:40,262
We'll send mummy shopping, dad

1480
01:56:40,804 --> 01:56:44,084
And the two of us will set out for
a healthy walk every evening

1481
01:56:44,724 --> 01:56:49,804
And I'll treat you to a couple of pegs
of the best whisky in the world

1482
01:56:50,244 --> 01:56:54,940
A couple of them is all right.
But they ought to be big ones

1483
01:56:55,078 --> 01:56:57,284
Oh yes, also tell him to
arrange for some crisps

1484
01:56:58,123 --> 01:56:59,779
Also the accompaniment, son.

1485
01:56:59,859 --> 01:57:04,060
We have worked hard
to make you feel proud of us, dad

1486
01:57:04,342 --> 01:57:08,142
Come and see for yourself, dad.
You'll have a lot of rest

1487
01:57:08,902 --> 01:57:12,182
And Dad, I forgot to tell you
the main thing

1488
01:57:12,502 --> 01:57:16,396
I have a surprise waiting for you!
- What surprise?

1489
01:57:16,589 --> 01:57:20,076
I'll tell you only when you
come here... yes, it's a surprise

1490
01:57:20,664 --> 01:57:23,224
Must hang up now. This call is
getting to be too expensive!

1491
01:57:27,541 --> 01:57:28,275
He is my son.

1492
01:57:32,268 --> 01:57:34,859
What's up sir?
You're in a good mood

1493
01:57:35,019 --> 01:57:38,539
From night lamp to tube light.
- Since the punk started the hotel..

1494
01:57:38,619 --> 01:57:40,334
Business is down in the dumps

1495
01:57:40,472 --> 01:57:43,627
After many days I've got a
good tourist group coming

1496
01:57:44,984 --> 01:57:48,097
Wish I'd known earlier. I'd have
sent them to Chantu's hotel

1497
01:57:48,270 --> 01:57:50,104
Did you say something?
- No. Who is coming?

1498
01:57:50,277 --> 01:57:53,833
Some folk attending
a college conference

1499
01:58:03,753 --> 01:58:06,233
Hurry up!
- Welcome to Goa

1500
01:58:10,273 --> 01:58:13,891
Welcome. Please come..

1501
01:58:15,607 --> 01:58:18,410
Holy shit! From where
did this imbecile come?

1502
01:58:21,175 --> 01:58:24,255
What are you doing here?
- He's the hotel manager

1503
01:58:24,335 --> 01:58:28,975
Do you know him?
- Do I? He studied in my college

1504
01:58:29,163 --> 01:58:32,754
Not studied... both of them
would give us lessons

1505
01:58:34,407 --> 01:58:40,695
Hey, listen. The guys whose tales
I narrated from Bombay to Goa...

1506
01:58:40,775 --> 01:58:43,223
Chantu and Bantu... This is Bantu..

1507
01:58:45,025 --> 01:58:47,505
Where is sly Chantu?

1508
01:58:47,665 --> 01:58:50,025
Sir, relax for a while.
We'll talk later

1509
01:58:50,105 --> 01:58:52,813
Is he also here?
- Who are you talking of?

1510
01:58:53,401 --> 01:58:57,595
He was a friend of mine.
- What? He never spoke of Chantu?

1511
01:58:57,675 --> 01:59:00,646
They were like peas in a pod.
- Really?

1512
01:59:00,726 --> 01:59:05,407
They can never break up.
They'd fool everyone

1513
01:59:05,766 --> 01:59:08,923
Sir, what are you saying?
- I'm praising you

1514
01:59:09,731 --> 01:59:13,066
They were masters.
They'll say, they're shaving...

1515
01:59:13,323 --> 01:59:15,923
They'll shave your head off
and you won't even realise

1516
01:59:16,366 --> 01:59:20,732
They make monkeys out of men.
- Sir, forget it. That's past

1517
01:59:20,905 --> 01:59:24,074
Yes but where is he?
- He's working elsewhere

1518
01:59:24,420 --> 01:59:27,042
Why?
- There was only one post here

1519
01:59:27,194 --> 01:59:30,123
Then create a vacancy.
Is he your boss?

1520
01:59:30,370 --> 01:59:31,843
Sayba.
- Sardesai

1521
01:59:32,701 --> 01:59:35,323
I'll give you an idea.
A million dollar idea

1522
01:59:35,600 --> 01:59:39,603
Create a vacancy in your
hotel and appoint Chantu

1523
01:59:39,683 --> 01:59:46,061
Once together, they'll throw
all hotels in Goa out of business

1524
01:59:46,141 --> 01:59:47,826
And your hotel will be tops

1525
01:59:47,906 --> 01:59:49,175
Really?
- Guarantee

1526
01:59:49,410 --> 01:59:51,029
But he never told me...

1527
01:59:51,548 --> 01:59:52,676
Get him.

1528
01:59:52,756 --> 01:59:55,291
I don't know where he is
He's very far...

1529
01:59:55,478 --> 01:59:57,672
Don't worry about money..

1530
01:59:59,234 --> 02:00:01,407
Listen!
- That's Chantu there!

1531
02:00:06,056 --> 02:00:09,183
Him...?
- Yes! The body builder! Mutton chop!

1532
02:00:09,331 --> 02:00:11,861
That's our sworn enemy.
How can they be friends?

1533
02:00:11,941 --> 02:00:13,091
Yes.

1534
02:00:13,171 --> 02:00:15,411
Are you joking?
You have to be

1535
02:00:15,971 --> 02:00:18,851
That's Chantu. How
can he be his enemy?

1536
02:00:20,883 --> 02:00:23,011
They must be conning somebody

1537
02:00:23,091 --> 02:00:25,411
Why are you saying this?

1538
02:00:26,397 --> 02:00:30,651
Tell the truth. Who is the victim?

1539
02:00:31,309 --> 02:00:32,749
Me.
- There you go

1540
02:00:33,392 --> 02:00:37,229
No...
- Shut up! Jaggu! Raja! Ram!

1541
02:00:37,502 --> 02:00:39,205
Damn you...!
- I messed things?

1542
02:00:39,285 --> 02:00:42,111
Major trouble!
- Rush down!

1543
02:00:42,191 --> 02:00:43,469
What...?

1544
02:00:45,404 --> 02:00:47,309
Where's he gone...?

1545
02:00:49,831 --> 02:00:53,431
Sardesai created trouble.
Sayba knows we're thick pals

1546
02:00:53,511 --> 02:00:56,613
You should've shut him up.
- I tried but he got carried away

1547
02:00:56,758 --> 02:00:58,872
I couldn't control him.
- You should've strangled him!

1548
02:00:58,952 --> 02:01:02,161
Forget about what happened.
Now how do we stop Sayba?

1549
02:01:02,542 --> 02:01:05,724
You go in. I'll manage him.
- Are you sure?

1550
02:01:05,804 --> 02:01:08,432
Yes. Where will he hide?
I'll dig him out!

1551
02:01:08,837 --> 02:01:11,152
You're hand in glove with him!
You...!

1552
02:01:16,289 --> 02:01:17,458
Get him!

1553
02:01:40,928 --> 02:01:42,650
Let go...!

1554
02:01:47,251 --> 02:01:48,691
Get the rascal!

1555
02:01:57,567 --> 02:02:00,003
Your game is up!

1556
02:02:20,106 --> 02:02:24,346
Killed my Sayba...!

1557
02:02:24,689 --> 02:02:28,546
Who killed my Sayba!

1558
02:02:28,746 --> 02:02:31,546
Who killed him?

1559
02:02:34,202 --> 02:02:35,546
Pedro... You?

1560
02:02:36,506 --> 02:02:40,066
Scoundrel! Who killed my brother?

1561
02:02:40,326 --> 02:02:43,405
I don't know. It was
going on for some days.

1562
02:02:43,485 --> 02:02:46,066
What's his name?
- Chantu

1563
02:02:47,683 --> 02:02:50,643
The cops are on my tail

1564
02:02:50,843 --> 02:02:53,403
I'll keep you informed
about where I'm hiding.

1565
02:02:53,963 --> 02:02:57,443
Let me know the moment
you find the boy. Got it?

1566
02:03:15,851 --> 02:03:16,811
Leaving?

1567
02:03:19,625 --> 02:03:22,611
I'm coming.
- When will you return?

1568
02:03:22,691 --> 02:03:26,251
Is this a five star hotel
that you ask when I'll return?

1569
02:03:26,451 --> 02:03:31,021
People who come here once
keep coming back for more

1570
02:03:31,101 --> 02:03:33,131
Not me but I'll send two guests.

1571
02:03:33,211 --> 02:03:39,931
The scamps because of whom
I landed here. Chantu-Bantu

1572
02:03:44,072 --> 02:03:45,959
I'm speaking.
- So am I

1573
02:03:46,118 --> 02:03:49,432
Pedro here!
- Oh. Are you well?

1574
02:03:50,749 --> 02:03:52,629
Did the stupid cops get you yet?

1575
02:03:52,709 --> 02:04:00,309
Till I nab my brother's killer,
even the god of death can't get me

1576
02:04:00,523 --> 02:04:04,432
Found Chantu?
- Not yet.

1577
02:04:04,631 --> 02:04:09,231
Pedro has no idea the man helping
him find his brother's killer...

1578
02:04:09,831 --> 02:04:12,191
himself is the killer's best friend

1579
02:04:12,871 --> 02:04:15,591
This news should be given to Pedro

1580
02:04:16,431 --> 02:04:17,951
But where the heck is he?

1581
02:04:18,111 --> 02:04:21,911
I'm hiding in the old cave.
Come here to inform me

1582
02:04:22,113 --> 02:04:27,873
If you tell anyone else,
I'll dig your grave here!

1583
02:04:28,027 --> 02:04:30,193
I get it. Okay

1584
02:04:44,033 --> 02:04:48,402
The hotel seems closed.
- Is it the right address?

1585
02:04:48,568 --> 02:04:51,087
The kids pulled a
fast one on us again

1586
02:04:51,246 --> 02:04:54,966
My son won't play
such a stupid prank

1587
02:04:55,564 --> 02:04:58,646
Your son!
- Where do we go? What do we do?

1588
02:04:59,892 --> 02:05:03,132
Are you the parents of Chantu-Bantu?
- That's right

1589
02:05:03,452 --> 02:05:07,452
I guessed right.
You look like their parents

1590
02:05:07,532 --> 02:05:11,692
Is that true?
- Do you know them?

1591
02:05:11,920 --> 02:05:14,252
I'm their manager.
- Okay...

1592
02:05:14,332 --> 02:05:17,812
They sent me here to fetch you.
They're in an urgent meeting

1593
02:05:17,974 --> 02:05:19,532
Hop in

1594
02:05:37,147 --> 02:05:39,572
What? Want to die?

1595
02:05:46,556 --> 02:05:47,652
What...?

1596
02:05:50,582 --> 02:05:53,182
You did the right thing
in coming straight to me

1597
02:05:54,064 --> 02:05:56,102
I have an old account
to square with Pedro.

1598
02:05:57,022 --> 02:06:01,142
Pedro is a dangerous criminal.
We'll besiege the cave with our force

1599
02:06:01,222 --> 02:06:03,022
Where's the inspector?
- This way

1600
02:06:03,735 --> 02:06:06,015
Gomes has kidnapped your parents!

1601
02:06:06,215 --> 02:06:10,255
But he was in jail...?
- He's out. And he's got your parents

1602
02:06:10,335 --> 02:06:12,015
Now he wants to meet you

1603
02:06:12,095 --> 02:06:15,975
Who is Gomes?
- He was our assistant manager

1604
02:06:16,055 --> 02:06:19,609
We caught him stealing. He was
jailed. Maybe he wants revenge

1605
02:06:19,752 --> 02:06:22,432
This is a major problem.
- Sir, there's a plan

1606
02:06:22,598 --> 02:06:24,792
Who has it?
- Him. Tell him...

1607
02:06:25,572 --> 02:06:26,832
The plan...

1608
02:06:30,339 --> 02:06:34,792
I know you and Chantu are pals

1609
02:06:35,058 --> 02:06:39,818
I want to tell Pedro.
- What will you gain?

1610
02:06:40,216 --> 02:06:44,096
I want to get your bones broken

1611
02:06:44,378 --> 02:06:49,016
And Pedro will do that for me.
You'll take me to Pedro

1612
02:06:49,193 --> 02:06:53,780
You know what I'll do to your
parents if you won't take me

1613
02:06:54,258 --> 02:06:56,336
You sent me to jail!

1614
02:06:58,516 --> 02:07:02,236
One thing can be done.
Play this game with Chantu

1615
02:07:03,169 --> 02:07:05,876
I'll give you Rs. 10 lakhs
for sparing my parent's life.

1616
02:07:06,366 --> 02:07:11,276
You'll get your revenge and the cash
- Fooling me, you dumb waiter!

1617
02:07:11,476 --> 02:07:15,636
Where will you get the cash?
- I'm marrying Khanna's daughter

1618
02:07:15,716 --> 02:07:19,837
I'm dead if you refuse later.
- But you can tell Pedro about me

1619
02:07:19,917 --> 02:07:22,556
Don't forget he's your best friend!

1620
02:07:23,766 --> 02:07:28,036
People kill their brother to save
their skin. He's just a friend

1621
02:07:29,636 --> 02:07:32,636
Friend to a scoundrel.
- I'm a dog

1622
02:07:35,398 --> 02:07:36,117
What's this?

1623
02:07:38,084 --> 02:07:42,524
Bantu put a microphone in Gomes'
pocket. Now we can hear him

1624
02:07:43,050 --> 02:07:44,724
But how...?
- Just a minute

1625
02:07:52,293 --> 02:07:55,604
Man, where have you brought me?
- Hold your horses...

1626
02:07:56,645 --> 02:07:59,844
Anyone there?
- Good God!

1627
02:08:00,637 --> 02:08:03,675
Nobody here

1628
02:08:09,098 --> 02:08:12,378
What's wrong?
- Nothing

1629
02:08:30,204 --> 02:08:33,804
Yes?
- It's me. Bantu

1630
02:08:34,650 --> 02:08:36,204
Why have you come here?

1631
02:08:37,884 --> 02:08:40,164
Who is he?
- He's Gomes

1632
02:08:40,330 --> 02:08:42,964
Wants to talk about Chantu.
- Where is he?

1633
02:08:43,244 --> 02:08:46,804
Will you come this way?
- What is it?

1634
02:08:48,749 --> 02:08:51,884
Pedro Sir, do you want
Chantu's whereabouts?

1635
02:08:52,396 --> 02:08:57,884
Bantu can give it.
Actually they're best pals

1636
02:08:57,964 --> 02:09:00,644
Together they were making
an idiot out of your brother

1637
02:09:00,823 --> 02:09:04,244
What nonsense!
- I'd have found out by now...

1638
02:09:04,490 --> 02:09:09,564
The cops haven't got here because
their parents are in my control

1639
02:09:09,644 --> 02:09:13,124
At a place nobody can doubt.
- Where?

1640
02:09:14,266 --> 02:09:16,528
I'll tell you later

1641
02:09:17,807 --> 02:09:21,007
He's a cad! Just won't
mention where he hid them

1642
02:09:21,247 --> 02:09:23,847
Or we'd have got them now.
- Now what happens?

1643
02:09:24,699 --> 02:09:27,207
Now we'll use... plan number two

1644
02:09:28,527 --> 02:09:35,607
If your news is wrong, I'll
crack your skull like a coconut

1645
02:09:35,948 --> 02:09:37,047
Get it?

1646
02:09:44,894 --> 02:09:51,509
Swine! Where's your pal?
- Mr. Pedro, my friend is no more

1647
02:09:52,015 --> 02:09:55,535
Your brother was my friend.
- Silence!

1648
02:09:56,415 --> 02:10:00,575
But he says, your friend
killed my brother

1649
02:10:01,335 --> 02:10:03,815
And you're working with the cops!

1650
02:10:04,923 --> 02:10:09,735
Such a big lie! Dear God,
why is this happening to me?

1651
02:10:10,064 --> 02:10:13,855
Actually, the cops have kept a reward
of half a million on your head

1652
02:10:14,021 --> 02:10:17,446
He's blackmailing me to get that.
He kidnapped my girl friend

1653
02:10:17,617 --> 02:10:22,061
He forced me to take him to you.
- He's lying! Pedro, he's pretending

1654
02:10:22,297 --> 02:10:25,657
You're acting!
- Gomes! Stop it!

1655
02:10:26,516 --> 02:10:29,449
Move!

1656
02:10:30,224 --> 02:10:31,217
Move back!

1657
02:10:31,977 --> 02:10:36,577
Are you all right, Bantu?
- How'd you get out of his captivity?

1658
02:10:38,076 --> 02:10:40,177
This servant of the rascal
Gomes brought some food

1659
02:10:40,257 --> 02:10:43,439
Seizing the opportunity,
I clubbed him and escaped

1660
02:10:43,756 --> 02:10:47,756
What are you doing here?

1661
02:10:47,836 --> 02:10:50,340
Who is he?
- ACP Pande

1662
02:10:50,420 --> 02:10:54,916
He was hiding and probably
listening to Radio Mirchi

1663
02:10:54,996 --> 02:11:00,777
Isn't that a wireless machine?
What were you listening to, on it?

1664
02:11:00,857 --> 02:11:03,156
Answer or I'll slaughter you!

1665
02:11:03,631 --> 02:11:06,391
Speak!
- Gomes gave us information

1666
02:11:06,671 --> 02:11:10,831
He'd lead us to you and
we're connected by wireless

1667
02:11:10,991 --> 02:11:16,143
There.
- Lies! It's a trick played by the cops

1668
02:11:16,337 --> 02:11:20,433
We'll know if the cop is lying.
Let's search him

1669
02:11:20,513 --> 02:11:24,071
Yes. - Stand straight.
Let me frisk you

1670
02:11:24,151 --> 02:11:28,111
I have nothing.
- We'll see

1671
02:11:31,413 --> 02:11:34,431
Pedro, my brother
this was in his pocket

1672
02:11:35,530 --> 02:11:39,231
What is it?
- It's called a microphone

1673
02:11:40,020 --> 02:11:46,631
5 miles away, the voice can
be heard through this machine

1674
02:11:46,787 --> 02:11:51,188
You hear it yourself.
- No, sir. They're pretending

1675
02:11:52,835 --> 02:11:55,951
1, 2, 3... that's it.

1676
02:11:59,027 --> 02:12:01,311
I'll settle scores with you later

1677
02:12:02,885 --> 02:12:04,725
I'll first make
mince meat out of you!

1678
02:12:05,206 --> 02:12:08,925
It's not my fault.
Listen to me. No!

1679
02:12:09,150 --> 02:12:11,365
One last chance. Listen...

1680
02:12:12,085 --> 02:12:16,565
I've locked their parents
in the jungle in a car

1681
02:12:16,801 --> 02:12:20,565
Get them here and
the truth will be clear

1682
02:12:20,845 --> 02:12:22,565
But put this away...

1683
02:12:24,280 --> 02:12:28,293
Out!

1684
02:12:28,373 --> 02:12:30,765
Who are you?
- C'mon

1685
02:12:37,845 --> 02:12:41,654
Yes! Here they are.
2 families together!

1686
02:12:41,806 --> 02:12:46,968
Come on.
- Welcome

1687
02:12:49,397 --> 02:12:53,673
You come here... you this way...

1688
02:12:54,150 --> 02:12:58,474
This is Mr. Pedro. Tell him that
you're Chantu and Bantu's parents

1689
02:12:58,654 --> 02:13:03,234
And Chantu and Bantu are
best friends since they were 4

1690
02:13:03,462 --> 02:13:06,062
But towards whom do we point?

1691
02:13:09,033 --> 02:13:11,822
Don't you recognize your own son?
- Must be the one who is tied

1692
02:13:12,762 --> 02:13:14,610
My son!

1693
02:13:15,011 --> 02:13:18,304
My darling! My love!

1694
02:13:18,385 --> 02:13:21,185
Whom is he kissing?
- what have they done to you?

1695
02:13:21,383 --> 02:13:23,425
That cad is a cop!

1696
02:13:24,234 --> 02:13:29,492
What do I do with you?
- Like the cheat Bantu...

1697
02:13:30,066 --> 02:13:32,505
his parents are cheats. By God!

1698
02:13:33,250 --> 02:13:37,815
Give me one chance.
I'll skin his parents!

1699
02:13:37,895 --> 02:13:39,650
Then I'll see how he screams!

1700
02:13:46,712 --> 02:13:49,853
You said you'd pay us.
Then why are you hitting us?

1701
02:13:55,091 --> 02:13:57,850
Confess that Bantu is your son!

1702
02:13:59,180 --> 02:14:00,342
Stop!

1703
02:14:05,118 --> 02:14:08,518
You never said you too
would be acting

1704
02:14:09,158 --> 02:14:13,798
Now, who are you?
- I'm Principal Sardesai

1705
02:14:14,118 --> 02:14:18,615
I run an acting school.
You must have heard of it

1706
02:14:18,844 --> 02:14:21,434
Here's my card. This man
came to me yesterday

1707
02:14:21,771 --> 02:14:25,674
Said, he'd give a chance
to our students in a film

1708
02:14:26,060 --> 02:14:29,754
You said, it's a role
of parents of 2 youngsters

1709
02:14:30,053 --> 02:14:33,474
You never mentioned whips.
We charge extra for that

1710
02:14:34,862 --> 02:14:36,633
Now what do you have to say?

1711
02:14:39,069 --> 02:14:41,674
Move. Acting school!!

1712
02:14:42,965 --> 02:14:45,914
I know this schmuck well

1713
02:14:46,106 --> 02:14:48,754
He's the Principal of
Chantu and Bantu's college

1714
02:14:49,005 --> 02:14:51,434
He's hand in glove with them.

1715
02:14:51,914 --> 02:14:54,674
They're all together.
- He's the only one separate

1716
02:14:54,830 --> 02:14:57,554
I'll show him!
- Don't hit me!

1717
02:14:57,634 --> 02:14:58,594
Stop!

1718
02:15:00,552 --> 02:15:03,437
Now who is she?
- No idea.

1719
02:15:03,700 --> 02:15:08,143
I'm a helpless woman
tormented by Chantu-Bantu

1720
02:15:08,750 --> 02:15:11,783
Gomes is right. Chantu
and Bantu are friends

1721
02:15:12,805 --> 02:15:17,150
Brother Pedro, they're responsible
for sending your brother to his grave

1722
02:15:17,383 --> 02:15:19,966
Do you have evidence?
- That's not needed

1723
02:15:20,046 --> 02:15:23,623
Whip the boy
and his mother will yell

1724
02:15:23,703 --> 02:15:26,823
My Bantu!!

1725
02:15:27,009 --> 02:15:33,343
A son may ignore his mother's pain
but a mother can't bear his agony

1726
02:15:35,463 --> 02:15:36,743
That's right.

1727
02:15:38,833 --> 02:15:41,343
Let's give it a try

1728
02:15:42,645 --> 02:15:45,503
Gomes, you get another chance

1729
02:15:45,641 --> 02:15:47,023
Get started.

1730
02:15:47,814 --> 02:15:49,063
Make way!

1731
02:15:51,073 --> 02:15:54,183
Now we'll know whose son you are

1732
02:15:58,020 --> 02:15:59,722
Don't beat him!

1733
02:16:04,018 --> 02:16:05,880
Stop!

1734
02:16:06,952 --> 02:16:09,338
Now what do you want?

1735
02:16:09,418 --> 02:16:15,379
This woman is a cheat. Bantu
caught her red handed in your hotel

1736
02:16:15,766 --> 02:16:18,246
She's seeking revenge.
- No!

1737
02:16:18,499 --> 02:16:23,726
Really? Didn't you come to our hotel
as Queen of Janakpur for a free meal?

1738
02:16:24,166 --> 02:16:28,566
She mixed glass in the pudding
and blackmailed the late Sayba

1739
02:16:28,686 --> 02:16:30,646
But that...
- Heard that?

1740
02:16:31,006 --> 02:16:32,766
Bantu had exposed her hoax.

1741
02:16:33,486 --> 02:16:37,566
I was demoted from Manager to
Laundry Manager because of him

1742
02:16:37,966 --> 02:16:41,166
But I'll only speak the truth

1743
02:16:44,447 --> 02:16:49,726
I can't bear it no more!
Now I'll fire a gun not the dagger!

1744
02:16:49,806 --> 02:16:53,046
Hold it.
- What the heck!

1745
02:16:53,276 --> 02:16:57,739
Now who is it?
- Hold on. Hear me out first

1746
02:16:59,131 --> 02:17:02,371
Whoever you are, don't say
Chantu-Bantu are friends...

1747
02:17:02,771 --> 02:17:06,011
and are in this together.
- Right, but first listen...

1748
02:17:06,091 --> 02:17:09,371
I'll show you. I have evidence

1749
02:17:09,771 --> 02:17:14,657
Here they are and that's
Mr. Khanna, the elder brother...

1750
02:17:19,998 --> 02:17:23,331
Now what do you have to say?

1751
02:17:28,052 --> 02:17:29,931
Now I'm convinced

1752
02:17:33,815 --> 02:17:36,914
Anybody there to stop me?

1753
02:17:38,146 --> 02:17:41,536
No one.
- Nobody... come on.

1754
02:17:41,681 --> 02:17:45,341
Move it. Come on!

1755
02:17:45,591 --> 02:17:50,111
I give you one minute
to tell where your pal is

1756
02:17:50,255 --> 02:17:52,351
Else I'll shoot everyone

1757
02:17:53,687 --> 02:17:57,540
You finish the rest
while I shoot him

1758
02:17:57,727 --> 02:18:01,151
I'll count to 3. One...

1759
02:18:01,532 --> 02:18:03,608
Two...
- Stop.

1760
02:18:07,801 --> 02:18:10,431
You! You're here, you jerk!

1761
02:18:10,928 --> 02:18:15,328
I'll first shoot you!
You've troubled me a lot!

1762
02:18:16,001 --> 02:18:17,648
Who threw the shoe?

1763
02:18:18,160 --> 02:18:20,208
Did you throw it? You...?

1764
02:18:20,288 --> 02:18:22,823
You?
You?

1765
02:18:23,273 --> 02:18:24,608
You?

1766
02:18:25,248 --> 02:18:26,368
Not me

1767
02:18:27,017 --> 02:18:30,728
It was you. Show me your foot!

1768
02:18:31,147 --> 02:18:33,408
Show me your foot!

1769
02:18:39,081 --> 02:18:41,081
Beat them up!

1770
02:18:44,924 --> 02:18:47,601
Let me go!
- Don't spare him!

1771
02:19:07,296 --> 02:19:10,842
My shoe! The shoe...

1772
02:19:17,738 --> 02:19:20,258
Freeze! Nobody moves!

1773
02:19:21,229 --> 02:19:22,538
Nobody moves!

1774
02:19:24,197 --> 02:19:25,938
Why are you laughing?

1775
02:19:27,656 --> 02:19:28,698
Shoe!

1776
02:19:33,282 --> 02:19:35,138
Threatening me with a shoe!

1777
02:19:36,147 --> 02:19:37,206
Let me wear it

1778
02:19:43,134 --> 02:19:47,597
Let me wear the shoe. I said,
time please! I'm just not ready...

1779
02:20:00,112 --> 02:20:03,872
I hear you give chance to new heroes.
- Yes

1780
02:20:04,161 --> 02:20:07,592
You have a great personality.
Here's my card

1781
02:20:08,271 --> 02:20:09,503
I'll make you a hero

1782
02:20:10,430 --> 02:20:12,072
Excuse me.
- Please...

1783
02:20:12,396 --> 02:20:13,592
Is she a heroine?
- Yes

1784
02:20:15,218 --> 02:20:16,472
You talk to anyone

1785
02:20:26,649 --> 02:20:29,853
Side! Or I'll break your head.
- No bullet in it

1786
02:20:33,264 --> 02:20:35,105
I can handle you with my legs

1787
02:20:40,322 --> 02:20:42,474
What a shot!

1788
02:20:47,653 --> 02:20:49,893
On whose side are you?
- Sir, but I'm your man!

1789
02:20:49,973 --> 02:20:52,413
Your laundry manager.
- Thank God

1790
02:20:54,133 --> 02:20:56,413
Get your clothes washed
for free in the laundry

1791
02:20:58,653 --> 02:20:59,613
Where's he gone?

1792
02:21:11,410 --> 02:21:13,540
Gill, move some more

1793
02:21:16,529 --> 02:21:19,863
You got my son whipped! You!

1794
02:21:21,897 --> 02:21:24,735
My son!
- She's caught us!

1795
02:21:24,942 --> 02:21:29,502
The mother not only cries but
uses the whip when her son is hurt

1796
02:21:29,737 --> 02:21:31,370
Don't you have men at home?
- Shut up!

1797
02:21:49,449 --> 02:21:50,729
Don't' be scared. Come on

1798
02:21:52,729 --> 02:21:55,649
Don't hide behind a woman. Come out!
- Face him!

1799
02:21:55,729 --> 02:21:58,089
He has a stick!
- Coward, come out!

1800
02:21:59,409 --> 02:22:02,009
Hit the man, don't talk.
- Holy smoke!

1801
02:22:02,089 --> 02:22:03,049
Shall we go?

1802
02:22:12,953 --> 02:22:15,033
Whose side are you on?
- Pedro's

1803
02:22:15,113 --> 02:22:17,326
So am I.
- Really?

1804
02:22:18,260 --> 02:22:19,513
I lied to you

1805
02:22:21,402 --> 02:22:23,673
Where has he gone?
I'm going home!

1806
02:23:11,858 --> 02:23:14,698
Mother! I am fine

1807
02:23:15,155 --> 02:23:17,138
Get the ambulance

1808
02:23:33,810 --> 02:23:35,263
Leave him!

1809
02:23:44,827 --> 02:23:47,285
My brother! Bantu!

1810
02:23:47,483 --> 02:23:49,627
You can't leave me alone!

1811
02:23:54,567 --> 02:23:55,867
My child!

1812
02:24:20,374 --> 02:24:24,054
The bullet just grazed your arm.
How did you get the other wounds?

1813
02:24:24,734 --> 02:24:29,734
What can I say?
A short prank proved costly

1814
02:24:29,990 --> 02:24:30,934
Meaning?

1815
02:24:31,486 --> 02:24:34,694
I pretended to die when shot

1816
02:24:35,534 --> 02:24:38,174
I held my breath as long as I could

1817
02:24:39,081 --> 02:24:41,854
But when I took a
breath after a minute...

1818
02:24:42,229 --> 02:24:49,502
I started laughing. Sundri,
Mundri and Chantu beat me up

1819
02:24:51,933 --> 02:24:53,214
You're a rogue

1820
02:24:56,146 --> 02:24:58,786
Now come and sit with the guests

1821
02:24:58,866 --> 02:25:01,146
We're coming. Just hold on

1822
02:25:01,226 --> 02:25:04,266
Your kids worked a miracle.

1823
02:25:04,409 --> 02:25:06,569
Something that wasn't working...

1824
02:25:06,769 --> 02:25:08,129
is now operational

1825
02:25:09,490 --> 02:25:12,089
Our resort was shut for years

1826
02:25:12,266 --> 02:25:15,809
They not only ran it
but ran it so capably...

1827
02:25:15,889 --> 02:25:18,441
that it's earning more
profits than our other resorts.

1828
02:25:18,521 --> 02:25:23,009
We're what you call it...
finding such good what's it..?

1829
02:25:26,787 --> 02:25:29,027
Happy to find such sons-in-law.

1830
02:25:29,667 --> 02:25:34,187
We'll take guru's blessings and
get them engaged and married soon

1831
02:25:34,450 --> 02:25:35,467
Guru?

1832
02:25:36,698 --> 02:25:41,627
He's not what you call it...
- No saint

1833
02:25:41,939 --> 02:25:44,265
An industrialist.
Totally detached

1834
02:25:44,680 --> 02:25:46,360
We worked for him

1835
02:25:46,575 --> 02:25:51,480
We initiate every good deed
of life with guru's blessings

1836
02:25:52,205 --> 02:25:54,254
There he comes!

1837
02:25:55,456 --> 02:25:59,280
Welcome.
- May you be happy

1838
02:26:02,319 --> 02:26:03,279
You!

1839
02:26:05,168 --> 02:26:08,519
What are these goons doing here?
- We're dead meat!
